args: Hmm? That voice from behind cover...\nWasn't thatâ€”
Celliera, that is enough already!\nNow please put your hands down.
Don't move, Elisanne. This will end it.\nI'll ease your suffering in an instant.
Ah, {player_name}! Have you\nalso come for one of my massages?
It was most terrifically painful,\nbut definitely worked wonders.
Thank you, Celliera. My training fatigue\nhas vanished.
By the way, Elisanne, your attacks have\na tendency to be slightly off center from\ntime to time, yes?
I could tell when I was massaging you.\nThe balance of your muscles is off\nbetween the two sides.
It shouldn't impact your overall combat\nreadiness, but a bit of intensive training\nmight remedy the imbalance.
You picked up on her weak point just by\ntouching her muscles?
Muscles tell much about a personâ€”\nlifestyle, mental state, and the like.
For example, Elisanne has recently\nbecome mindful of overeating, and\nhas ramped up her abdominal regimen.
And further, she has noted that the extra\nmuscle mass has made her clothes fit\ntighter than she'd like.
And she's quite embarrassed about that.\nParticularly when she's around you.
I'm still not sure I follow, but, um...\nI'll take your word for it.
I can't believe she read me that well just\nfrom touching me. Ugh.
Wait. If I could use that ability of hers,\nI just might be able to solve our little\nproblem...
Celliera? I need your help.\nMight you give me a hand?
That's the man you spoke of, yes?
Indeed. He's with a gang of thieves, but\nwithout sufficient evidence to pin them\ndown, they're running free.
The one who keeps lying and pretending\nnot to know anything?
Right. Which is why I want Celliera to\nexpose his lies and shine the light of\nday on his misdeeds.
I'd also be grateful if you could get him to\ndivulge the whereabouts of his associates.
We'll be on standby at a remote location.
Ho there, young man! You look strong.\nCare to arm wrestle?
The heck ya talkin' about, lady? Buzz off!
Are you certain? If you beat me,\nI'll do anything you tell me to.
Even mow my lawn?! ...Yeah, all right.\nBut no take-backs if ya don't wanna\ndo what I say!
You're sure singing a different tune now.\nVery well. Ready...and...GO!
Likewise! You certainly live up to your\nreputation as a member of a rowdy band\nof thieves, don't you?!
Hey, ya got the wrong idea about me.\nI'm a well-adjusted citizen!
Now then! Everyone gets nervous when\nthey lieâ€”and when they get nervous,\ntheir muscles stiffen up.
When I mentioned the band of thieves,\nyour arm muscles stiffened for just an\ninstant.
Then I suppose it wasn't you and your\nassociates who broke into that aristocrat's\nmanor some days back?
And the attack on the mail wagon\nlast month? Or the muggings out\non the highway?
I got no idea what you're on about.
Hmm... Perhaps those weren't ALL your\ndoing after all...
You really don't seem to know anything\nabout the mail-wagon incident...
Stop! There's no running away!\nI'm not letting your hand go!
OWWWWW! Your grip's like freakin' iron!
Give in! You're one of those dirty thieves\nand everyone knows it!
If you cooperate and tell us where the\nothers are, I'll ensure you're treated well.
OWWWW! I ain't tellin' ya a damn thing,\nlady! And if ya don't let go of me,\nyou're in for a world of pain!
Still resisting, eh? I'm almost impressed.
If that's how it's going to be, then I'll just\nhave to try another approach!
She dragged him behind the shop...
Lemme go... Hey! H-hey, wait! No way!\nOh, ya gotta be kiddin' me!
Ah, there they are. Goodness, but he looks\nwell worked-over.
I believe I told you to say ï¼‚ma'amï¼‚ when\nyou're talking, did I not?
F-forgive me, ma'am! I'm a member of the\nband of thieves, ma'am!
I'll tell you all of my misdeeds, ma'am!\nAND I'll lead you to my friends, ma'am!
What in the world did you do to him,\nCelliera?
I just gave him one of my little massages!
